_meanings:
{@--1@} Recognition;  
{#tadaBijYAnahetorhi dattaM tena mahAtmanA#} <ls>Rām.</ls> ({#aBijYAna#}
is a combination of {#anuBava#} or direct
perception and {#smfti#} or recollection;
a sort of direct perception 
assisted by the memory; as when we
say ‘this is the same man I saw
yesterday’ {#soyaM hyo dfzwo naraH, anuBava#} or
direct perception leading to the
identification expressed by {#ayaM#}
and the memory leading to the
reference to past action 
expressed by {#saH#}).

{@--3@} ({%a%}) A sign or token of 
recognition (person or thing); {#vatsa#} 
{#yoginyasmi mAlatyaBijYAnaM ca DArayAmi#} <ls>Māl. 9</ls>;
<ls>Bk. 8. 118</ls>, <ls n="Bk. 8.">124</ls>; <ls>R. 12. 62</ls>;  
<ls>Me. 112</ls>; {#upapannEraBijYAnErdUtaM tamavagacCata#}
<ls>Rām.</ls>
